 <body>
  <p>Integration between Adobe Campaign and Adobe Target (Classic and Standard) within Adobe Marketing Cloud allows you to insert a dynamic image from Adobe Target into an Adobe Campaign email delivery.</p> 
  <p>This integration allows recipient to receive email sent via Adobe Campaign including a dynamic version of the content thanks to Adobe Target. This dynamic version is computed depending on the rules specified beforehand when creating the email. </p> 
  <p>Several types of data can be used by Adobe Target:</p> 
  <ul>
   <li><p>Data from the Adobe Campaign datamart</p> </li>
   <li><p>Segments linked to the visitor ID in Adobe Target, if the data used is not subject to legal limitations</p> </li>
   <li><p>Adobe Target data: user agent, IP address, geolocalization data</p> </li>
  </ul>
  <p>For information on the integration between Adobe Campaign and Adobe Target, you can also refer to the <a href="https://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/target/a4t/c_campaign_and_target.html">Adobe Target Portal</a>.</p> 
